Reasoning: The paper discusses the Indus script and its potential use in economic transactions, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques (cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.DL). The use of stamp seals and tablets for administration and record-keeping also involves computational methods (cs.CC). The paper also draws parallels with other ancient scripts, which may fall under the category of historical computing (cs.HC) but this is less likely given the focus on the Indus script specifically.
